Heap
    1. heap have min/ max heap
    2. heap is always an complete tree!!! which we can use index to find parent or child
    3. but we can only access top node which is the min or max
    4. insert pop get update
        i. heapify O(n), will explain later on this page
        ii. insert O(logn) because when every a node insert to the heap, it will start on the last node position and
            track back to the position it should be, and the height is max logn
        iii. delete O(logn) why delete logn //TODO
        iv. update = delete + insert
        v. get O(1) only get the top node
    5. similar to 2, we can find the parent or child in O(1)
        Give current index x;
        Parent = (x - 1) / 2;
        Child1 = 2x + 1;
        Child2 = 2x + 2;


